The Office shall:
Assist the counties in developing an acceptable recycling plan required under § 9-1703 of this subtitle and § 9-505 of this title, including technical assistance to the local governments;
Coordinate the efforts of the State to facilitate the implementation of the recycling goals at the county level;
Review all recycling plans submitted as part of a county plan as required under § 9-505 of this title and advise the Secretary on the adequacy of the recycling plan; and
Administer the Statewide Electronics Recycling Program under Part IV of this subtitle.

Beginning on January 1, 1990, and biannually thereafter, the Office shall, in coordination with the Maryland Environmental Service, study and report to the Governor and, subject to § 2-1246 of the State Government Article, the General Assembly on:
The availability of local, national, and international markets for recycling materials;
The identification and location of recycling centers, including an analysis of existing recycling centers and the need to expand these facilities or construct new recycling centers;
Programs necessary to educate the public on the need to participate in recycling efforts;
The economics and financing of existing and proposed systems of waste disposal and recycling;
State procurement policies for the purchase of recycled materials;
Programs necessary to reduce the amount of solid waste generated for disposal by a State agency or unit;
The liaison role with local governments, the federal government, and the private sector;
The percentage reduction in the amount of solid waste that has been achieved by each county; and
Economically feasible methods for the recycling of scrap automobile tires, batteries, and white goods.
